7^{999999}\equiv a\pmod{1000}
\varphi
7^{-1} \equiv 143
 \varphi(1000) = \varphi(2^35^3) = (8-4)(125-25) = 400 
 7^{400} \equiv 1 \pmod{1000} 
 7^{999999} \equiv 7^{399} \equiv 7^{-1} \pmod{1000} 
 143\cdot 7 - 1000 = 1 
7^{999999}
7^{\phi (1000)} ≡ 1 \mod 1000 
\phi(1000) = 1000\cdot(1-\frac{1}{2})\cdot(1-\frac{1}{5})=400
7^{400}≡1 \mod 1000 
999999=400\cdot 2500-1
7^{399}\mod 1000
7^2=49=50-1,7^4=(50-1)^2=50^2-2\cdot50\cdot1+1^2=1+2400
7^{20}=(7^4)^5=(1+2400)^5=1+\binom512400+\binom52(2400)^2+\cdots\equiv1\pmod{1000}
999999\equiv-1\pmod{100}\equiv-1\pmod{20}
7^{999999}\equiv7^{-1}\pmod{1000}
\text{Now, }\frac{1000}7=142+\frac67=142+\frac1{\frac76}=142+\frac1{1+\frac16}
\displaystyle\frac{1000}7
\displaystyle142+\frac1{1+\frac11}=\frac{143}1
\displaystyle\implies 7^{-1}\equiv143\pmod{1000}
